To set the text color to red in CSS, you use the `color` property. You can specify the color using a named color, a hex code, an RGB value, or other color formats.

Here are the most common ways to do it:

**1. Using a named color (simplest):**
```css
p {
  color: red;
}
```

**2. Using a hex code:**
```css
p {
  color: #ff0000;
}
```

**3. Using RGB values:**
```css
p {
  color: rgb(255, 0, 0);
}
```

**Example in context:**
If you want to apply this to all paragraph elements in your HTML, your CSS would look like this:

```css
p {
  color: red;
}
```

And your HTML:
```html
<p>This text will be red.</p>
```

